wsdl:operation.name: CheckLogin
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This webservice authenticates a webshop account login, When the authentication is succesfull, the CustomerNr and type is returned, which can be used in further operations.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
UserName: The username of the webshop account that needs to be authenticated.
Password: The password that is supplied by the users.
IpAddres (optional): Trade also supports 'admin@admin.com' as a special administrator user (for example, to acces a administration panel in your webshop). To use this, an IP address that is allowed to login as admin must be set in the Trade settings. When an authorization request is send for admin login the IP address must be supplied, and Trade will check if it is allowed to login as an admin.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: Authentication succesfull
UserNotFound: An webshop account with the supplied username could not be found or the account is not active.
CustomerNotFound: The customer details of the webshop account could not be found or the customer is not active.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
LoginFailed: Authentication failed the supplied username and password.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: ForgotPassword
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used of a customer has lost the password of his webshop account. An email will be sent to the customer containing the link that is supplied. That link should point to a page that uses the SetForgotPassword operation to save a new password.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
UserName: The username of the webshop account of which the password has been lost.
ResetPageUrl: A full url to the page where the customer can set a new password.
ResetToken: A random generated token. The same token should be used to perform the SetForgotPassword operation. If the tokens supplied in this operation and the SetForgotPassword operation does not match, Trade will denied the SetForgotPassword request. The Token should be at least 256 characters long.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
UserNotFound: An webshop account with the supplied username could not be found or the account is not active.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
NoToken: There was no token supplied or token is too short.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: GetProducts
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used to get a list of available products and it's details. The list can be filtered using the input parameters.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
HomePage: Set this parameter to true to only request the products that are marked as "Show on homepage".
CustomerNr (optional): Add a CustomerNr to enrich the list of products with products specific for the given CustomerNr. If this paramet is used, it is mandatory to supply the CustomerType.
CustomerType (optional): Specify the customer type of the supplied CustomerNr.
CategoryId (optional): Specify the CategoryId to request only the products in a specific category.
ProductType (optional): Specify the ProductType to request only the products of a specific type. Valid inputs are: "Card", "E_Card" and "Other".

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
CustomerNotFound: The customer details of the webshop account could not be found or the customer is not active.
NoProduct: No products could be found, based on the supplied parameters.
NoCustomerType: A CustomerNr was specified, but no CustomerType was supplied.
ProductTypeNotValid: The supplied ProductType is not valid.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: GetProductImage
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used to retrieve the product images for a specified product. The images are encoded in Base64 format.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
ProductCode: The code of the product for which the images needs to be retrieved.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
NoImage: There are no images available for the supplied product code.
ProductNotValid: The supplied product code is invalid. The product does not exist or is not active.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: GetProductCategories
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used to retrieve a list of available product categories.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
ProductType (optional): Specify the ProductType to request only the categories which contain products of a specific type. Valid inputs are: "Card", "E_Card" and "Other".

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
ProductTypeNotValid: The supplied ProductType is not valid.
NoCategories: There were no categories found (no categories configured at all or for the specified product type).
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
CustomerNotFound: The customer could not be found or is not active.
NoCustomerType: No CustomerType was supplied.
NoOrders: The customer has no orders in Trade.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: CreatePreOrder
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used to create a new order in Trade. The order will be created with a pre-order status and the order number is returned. With this order number, the complete calculated (including VAT, discounts and surcharges) order details can be retrieved using the GetOrderDetails operation if needed. Before the order will be really processed, the ApprovePreOrder operation must be used.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
CustomerNr: Specify the customer number for which the new orders needs to be created..
CustomerType: Specify the customer type of the supplied CustomerNr.
NewOrder: The details of the order that needs to be created.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
NoCustomerType: There is no customer type supplied.
CustomerNotFound: The customer could not be found or the customer is not active.
OrderDataNotValid: Invalid order data was supplied (details speficied in result description).
NoOrderLines: There were no orderlines with products supplied.
InvalidOrderLine: Invalid orderline data was supplied (details speficied in result description).
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: ApprovePreOrder
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used approve an order that is created via the CreatePreOrder operation. When it is approved, the order will enter the normal orderflow in Trade.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
OrderNr: The number of the order that is approved.
PrePaid: Determines if Trade should handle the order as prepaid, and the order does not have to wait for payment. If this is specified as true, supplying transaction information is mandatory.
TransactionInfo (optional): If prepaid=true, this fiels is mandatory. Use it to specify all appropriate information about the payment transaction.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
OrderNotValid: An order with the supplied order number could not be found or is not in the correct (pre-order) state.
NoTransactionInfo Prepaid was specified as true, but there was no valid transaction information supplied.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: CreateCompany
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used to register a new company (Business Customer). The webservice will return the new company's CompanyNr.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
WsCompany: Set of details of the new company.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
InvalidCountry: A supplied Countrycode is not valid. Use 'GetCountries' to get available countries and supply the mentioned Letters_3 code
DuplicateCompany: A Company with the supplied COC number already exists!.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: GetCompany
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
CompanyNr (optional): The number of the company for which the details needs to be retrieved.
COCnumber (optional): The COC number of the company for which the details needs to be retrieved. This can be used for example to check if a specific COC number is already registered in Trade. Leave the CompanyNr empty to use this.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
CompanyNotFound: A Company could not be found or the company is not active.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: CreateAccount
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used to create a new webshop account for a specified customer.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
CustomerNr: Specify the customer number for which the new webshop account needs to be created..
CustomerType: Specify the customer type of the supplied CustomerNr.
WsWebshopAccount: Details of the webshop account that has to be created (username\EmailAddress and password).

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
CustomerNotFound: The customer could not be found or the customer is not active.
NoCustomerType: There is no customer type supplied.
CustomerHasAccount: The specified customer already has an active webshop account.
LoginInUse: The requested username is already in use.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: UpdateAccount
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
UserName: The webshop account current username.
Password: The webshop account current password.
NewUsername (optional): The webshop account new username.
NewPassword (optional): The webshop account new password.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
LoginFailed: Authentication failed the supplied username and password.
LoginInUse: The requested username is already in use.
UserNotFound: The webshop account could not be found or it is not active.
NoInput: Neither a new username or new password was supplied.

wsdl:operation.name: UpdateCompany

ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: SetForgotPassword
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used to set an new password for a webshop account after a ForgotPassword operation. The ForgotPassword operation must be less then 60 minutes back.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
UserName: The webshop account username.
NewPassword: The webshop account new password.
ResetToken: The reset token which was generated and send in the ForgotPassword operation.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
UserNotFound: An webshop account with the supplied username could not be found or the account is not active.
Expired: The ForgotPassword request is more then 1 hour old. The request is expired.
TokenIncorrect: The supplied token does not match the token that was supplied in the ForgotPassword request.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.

wsdl:operation.name: QuotePreOrder
wsdl:operation.wsdl:documentation:
This operation can be used to get a quote for an order that is created via the CreatePreOrder operation. The order status will be changed to "Quote" and a quote document will be returned in Base64 format. Use of this function is only allowed when the appropriate modules are present.

INPUT:
ProductOwnerNr (optional): The productowner id, which is supplied by Intersolve.
OrderNr: The number of the order that is approved.

RESULT CODES:
Ok: The operation completed succesfully.
ProductOwnerNotValid: ProductOwner could not be determined.
NotAllowed The appropriate module is not present, please contact sales.
OrderNotValid: An order with the supplied order number could not be found or is not in the correct (pre-order) state.
ServiceFailed: An unknown error occured during the webservice request.
